ADDITIONAL TERMS FOR REKO

1. AUTHORISED USE ONLY
   This tool is intended exclusively for:
   - Penetration testing of systems you own
   - Systems for which you have explicit written authorisation to test
   - Controlled lab environments (e.g. Metasploitable, HackTheBox, TryHackMe)
   - Academic research and CTF competitions

2. PROHIBITED USE
   You may NOT use this tool to:
   - Scan or probe systems without explicit written permission
   - Attack production systems, critical infrastructure, or public services
   - Facilitate unauthorised access to computer systems
   - Conduct denial-of-service attacks

3. LEGAL NOTICE
   Unauthorised scanning and penetration testing is illegal under:
   - Computer Fraud and Abuse Act (CFAA) - United States
   - Computer Misuse Act - United Kingdom
   - IT Act 2000 (Section 43, 66) - India
   - And equivalent laws in most jurisdictions worldwide

   The author assumes NO liability for any misuse of this tool.
   By using this software you agree that you are solely responsible
   for ensuring your use complies with all applicable laws.

4. RESEARCH CONTEXT
   Reko was developed as part of M.Tech research in Cyber Security at
   Sardar Patel University of Police, Security and Criminal Justice (SPUPSC)
   under the guidance of Dr. Arjun Choudhary and Dr. Vikas Sihag.

   Academic Session: 2025-2027
   Author: Mayan Suthar

5. ATTRIBUTION
   If you use Reko in research, publications, or presentations, please cite:

   Suthar, M. (2025). Reko - An Automated Active and Passive Network
